##Doctor Peng Yinhua's last battle

Wechat, bingdianweekly

Features, China Youth Daily's in depth reporting brand. We believe that news has more than one day of life.

If 2020 doesn't come, 29-year-old Peng Yinhua will still be living a normal life. He's slow, he doesn't say no, he's a workaholic, he plays video games when he's relaxed. He took out a student loan, and his father had a stroke, the backbone of both families. He's going to be a father, and he's working his ass off to buy a house.
But 2020 is here. In Wuhan, where the outbreak was spreading, he was a doctor at Jiangxia District's First People's Hospital, where he never flinched and eventually contracted the infection. On February 20, he died of organ failure. Peng Yinhua is a striver, is the kind of hard-working young people in our society. He became a hero during the outbreak.

By Liu Yang and Sandy Lamb

Freezing point story hardcore

Postpone the wedding

Peng returned home for the last time on January 18, the day after work, he did not mention the hospital to his wife, only said more and more busy. Peng Yinhua is a quiet person. In two weeks, they will have a wedding, and in three more months, a baby will be born. After two years of marriage, Zhong Xin knew that her husband had been trying to squeeze in time to make enough preparations for the wedding to give her a surprise.

But the outbreak has him increasingly worried. As early as December 20 last year, he was in the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia district. He was diagnosed with a severe case of "viral lung" in three departments and was transferred to the Central Hospital of Wuhan seven days later, later transferred to the treatment of infectious disease patients in the gold and Silver Lake Hospital. Word spread quickly that SARS was back, and was later corrected to viral pneumonia of unknown origin. By January 10, the aspiration department had set up a special ward with 60 beds, but within 10 days it was full.

Four days later, Peng Yinhua attended the general consultation of the hospital, was busy until the early morning, two "viral lung" patients still did not stay, one died in the inhalation of three branches, one transferred to the infected area after death.

Worried that his family and his pregnant wife were infected, Peng Yinhua decided to live in the department, schedule also shouted, "you foreign, have children all go home for the new year, row over the class I take. ". The wedding invitations are in the office drawer, "scheduled" after the time down to minutes, Peng Yinhua want to postpone, but colleagues Jiang Junxia said, "anything can be postponed, marriage can not. ".

The situation is getting more and more urgent. This new type of pneumonia was confirmed on January 20 as "human-to-human transmission. " The number of fever outpatients increased sharply that night. Many people did have problems when they had CT scans. Even if they did not have fever, there were plenty of people with chest tightness, shortness of breath, cough and sore throat. Many patients had underlying diseases, the family was in critical condition when they brought him in. That night, doctors and nurses stayed up all night.

The number of patients was increasing rapidly, and the respiratory division took over the two floors and set up a second group of quarantined wards, ready to admit patients in one day with zoning, training and secondary protection. Chen Hao, the department head, realized that the battle had already begun. Counting himself, it's seven doctors in three different specialties, all post'80s and'90s.

"I was in high school when SARS hit. The task was also quite urgent. As soon as the building was cleared, patients rushed to the building, " Jiang said, rice are too busy, at noon in the department to eat a bite, order by Peng Yinhua to help to get.

On that day, Peng Yinhua called his wife Zhong Xin and decided to postpone the wedding. "It's going to be a hard battle, " he said. His wife had a hospital in Jiangxia 120 do first aid nurses, no objection, only afraid of the husband's body can not stand, let him relax. "Don't worry, " Ms. Peng said.

Pang yin-wah

In the history of war

On the night of the 21st, as the agitation began to spread, patients crowded into the nurses'station and rushed forward. Peng has been standing there, trying to placate. "We will do our best to bring everyone in for treatment, " Dr. Yin later recalled repeating in a gentle voice. Order was restored in the middle of the night.

Perhaps only those who share this experience will understand the importance of patience. Li Yingpu, a colleague, worked the night shift and didn't eat dinner. He put on a protective suit at 5 p.m. until 8 a.m. the next day, "almost non-stop to see patients, write the test form, saw 80 numbers, but also to re-visit, that is 160 numbers, no water, no toilet. " That night Li Yingpu opened more than 20 hospital admission cards, all double lung ground glass lesions. And the ward has been overloaded with work, colleagues called, "fever clinic a little bit slow, the ward is really too busy. ". But Li Yingpu did not dare to let the patients out of the hospital.

"I've never seen so many patients, " Dr. Jiang said. In less than 24 hours, two floors, plus an emergency room, 130 beds are fully occupied.

The air is filled with anxiety and panic, some patients feel locked up, "like prison" , psychological unbearable, with doctors and nurses quarrel, "I want to leave the hospital, will be discharged, I died, even if death at home. ".

On the afternoon of the 22nd, an elderly male patient with various index drop, weak vital signs, Peng Yinhua began to rescue, and he was urgently transferred to the critical area, and communicate with his family, "may not have a good prognosis, " soon after the patient still left. At night, the 33-bed patient can not endure, the family's youngest son has been shouting, "you give me rescue! " Peng Yinhua for the elderly cardiopulmonary resuscitation, press for a couple of hours, the family is still not willing to give up, and shouted: "Another half-hour Press! "

Jiang Junxia also participated in the rescue, she knew it was in vain, but Peng Yinhua has been press. She also knows that this is Peng Yinhua, can not bear to refuse anyone. "The patient and his family are quite convinced that he will be a great doctor with his sense of responsibility, " Jiang said later.

Li Yingpu also has always known that Peng Yinhua does things in fact, can eat bitterness, regardless of returns. "He was the only male doctor in our department except for the chief, who had better physical and energy and was always ahead of the curve, " she recalled, examining patients, "You say, 'Dr. Peng, give me a hand, ' and he'll be here in a minute. Anything comes up and he's asked to cover, and Dr. Peng is happy to help. "

But right now, everyone's in over their heads. The patient in bed 60 was ineffectual, the family didn't understand, and the doctors had to explain what was at stake for a long time. Two days later, the family came for the death certificate, caught up with the computer problem, became impatient, began to lose his temper, break the table, break the stool. "We have to take in patients and deal with such things, " Jiang said.

The hospital later had 5 physicians to the isolation ward to support, but professionally still to the respiratory department, 7 doctors, 11 nurses around the clock. Li Yingpu and Peng Yinhua are on different floors. They were too busy to meet each other. At the same time, Peng Yinhua also had to support the clinic, morning is Jiang Junxia, afternoon is him, "get very late to work, simply can not get it. "

Jiang Junxia said that for the first two days after opening the isolation ward, every time Peng Yinhua was in the main class, he tried to treat patients alone, let the doctors in the day class rest, and also reduce the exposure opportunities of his colleagues. One afternoon, the patients were suddenly increased again before calling the doctors in the day class to help. "normally he wouldn't ask for help, but he couldn't take it anymore. "

In accordance with the government's deployment, Jiangxia District's designated hospital for new cases of coronary pneumonia was initially located at the Jiangxia District Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine, and the First Hospital in Jiangxia was notified to transfer all patients in the isolation ward to the Chinese Medicine Hospital. After transferring more than 100 patients, we were informed that Jiangxia Hospital was also designated as a fixed-point hospital —— -- because at that time, the 300 beds in traditional Chinese Medicine Hospital were not enough.

Less than two days later, the ward released more than 100 beds again filled. "I really dare not let the patients go. If they go into society and continue to infect others, it will still be a doctor's job in turn, and even more unbearable, " Chen said.

Those days, Peng and his colleagues complemented each other, taking turns treating patients. In the midst, Chen felt an unprecedented tension, "everyone is very tense. "

His understanding of the virus had also improved, and he now knew that it had a different mechanism than the previous knowledge system. The overwhelming infection made it difficult for him not only to push a large number of patients in front of him, but also to sneak around the defense line and invade his team.

"looks like we won the bid. "

Before the Lunar New Year's Eve, Peng Yinhua had a fever and was not in good spirits. His colleagues were very alert and immediately urged him to have a CT scan. At that time, he did not see any lesions in his lungs. He thought it was just a common cold. But on the first day of the Lunar New Year, he was still not in good spirits, poor appetite, help colleagues to pick up the meal, but they can not eat a few mouthfuls, re-examination of CT, there is an infection in the lung, but the nucleic acid test is negative.

Colleagues Remember, Peng Yinhua pretended to relax, said with a smile, "seems to have won the bid, " but all in the work. Director Chen Hao hurriedly let him stop work, live in isolation ward.

"In any case, cooperate with the treatment and come back to the front line when you are better, " Peng told Chen, adding that he would take over the management of patients in the quarantine zone and keep other doctors in the office and the clean area as much as possible to reduce exposure risks. "He knows the rest of us are very nervous about our work, " said Chen, who was shaken but did not agree to Dr. Peng's request. "doctors are probably more confident about themselves. Dr. Peng has just had an attack, and the symptoms are not very severe. "

As a doctor, Peng Yinhua especially knows how to cooperate with the treatment, in the department's Wechat group to tell everyone the feeling of disease, ECG monitor photos, inform the parameters of high-flow oxygen, non-invasive Suction machine, his temperature, his breathing rate, his Oxygenation, they're all being watched in real time. Chen Hao would also from time to time advise him to make some adjustments to the oxygen concentration, oxygen pressure to how much, sitting or lying down, and then observe his reaction, once saw signs of improvement.

In the early days, there was a severe shortage of protective materials in the first hospital in Jiangxia. Doctors and nurses wore protective clothing for seven or eight hours, sweating heavily and their goggles fogged up. It was difficult to draw blood from patients. Some doctors even dare not leave the isolation ward after rescuing the critically ill patients, for fear that the patients'condition will be repeated. All the paramedics were at their limit, and at 2:00 a.m. , someone in a Hazmat suit fell asleep at the nurses'station.

"Our work is also a long-term battle, which is not in line with the hospital sense, protection standards, but doctors have to carry it out, " Yin said. However, as many in the medical profession know, if a health care worker is overworked, all the precautions may not work.

"after a colleague was infected, close contacts were quarantined. Those days when everyone ate and slept together in the department, it could unfortunately form an infected environment, " Chen said, "But at that time, even though Peng Yinhua had already fallen ill and other colleagues couldn't get a rest, we were always on the same line, and to dump one person meant that the work was more difficult. "

"with Dr. Peng, our department was undoubtedly the hardest to fight in those first days, " Chen said. Until the Jiangsu medical team arrived ten days later, other doctors also transferred to support, Chen Hao felt that the department of more than 10 people can be considered smooth tone. But after Peng Yinhua, the Department of Yin Dequn, Jiang Junxia, Xu Hui have also found the infection focus, but no one expected, the youngest and physically strong Peng Yinhua, will be the one of rapid deterioration of the disease.

Colleagues together to the isolation ward to visit Peng Yinhua

Another organ failure, another..

New Year's Day, Zhong Xin received a phone call from Peng Yinhua, her husband in hospital, told her he was just a low-grade fever, cough, a little tired. Three days later, the husband called and said the nucleic acid test was positive for the first time. They decided not to tell their parents.

That afternoon, colleagues went to see Peng Yinhua. They talked and laughed, talked about going out for a good time together no matter what, and then mentioned going to make a scene at his wedding, "It's really romantic for your wife to wear a wedding dress with her stomach in the future. " "This wedding should not only wait for you to recover from your illness, but also for the end of the epidemic in Wuhan. By then, the baby may already be born, and the wedding of a family of three will be held. That's also very romantic. " When patients can be a little less, we do not have so tired, can have some time to go home to spend with their families.

Later, several infected doctors and nurses in the department set up a "refueling group" , where they cheered each other up every day. Some nurses were afraid. In the group, Peng Yinhua told them about the natural evolution of the disease, consoling them that it was not terrible, "It's like climbing a mountain. You're at the foot of the mountain when you get sick, you're on the mountainside when you get symptoms, you don't go straight down, you go up the mountain, you get your immunity back, you push the virus down, you go downhill, you go back down the mountain. "

On January 30, Dr. Jiang Junxia also checked into Peng Yinhua's ward and found that he was almost a changed man, breathing heavily when he moved. He used high-flow oxygen, and the oxygen concentration had been adjusted to 40 liters. It was difficult to eat, and it was even more difficult to move, can't get out of bed to go to the bathroom. Jiang Junxia brought him some milk. He couldn't drink it. Chen Hao found that his illness was progressing rapidly and tried to take care of him in the ward that day. Chen suggested that if the hospital could buy an ECMO, the department would hire Concorde professors to guide the use. But the thought of Peng Yinhua going to Ecmo made colleagues feel sad.

In the evening, Peng Yinhua will transfer to the infectious disease area (the serious disease area) , he asked Jiang Junxia, "Jiang teacher, why should I transfer to the Infectious Disease Area? " Jiang Junxia did not think much, said, "there is a big machine there. ". Chen Hao is afraid of him to worry, hurriedly say, "also not like this, go there to have its benefit" .

A few hours later, his condition got worse and he was transferred to the Golden Pool Hospital overnight. "We actually breathed a sigh of relief that night, " Jiang said. "We felt he was more secure and safe when he went to the gold and Silver Lake. ".

Just transferred to the gold and Silver Lake that two days, Peng Yinhua in good condition, did not use too many drugs, antibiotics are down. Colleagues in the group joke, let him learn the Good Treatment Program, the secret book back. Peng Yinhua replied, "let's just say I studied at the Golden Pond. ".

But soon, he began to warm up. Chen said, everyone's heart again, "we often accompany his illness and mood fluctuations, he is not in good condition when we are particularly depressed, better we are very excited. "

Her heart rate soared, she breathed harder, and her colleagues were in a state of shock, knowing that the disease had damaged the heart, not just the lungs.

I heard it was a top-of-the-line antibiotic -- A drug-resistant or fungal infection. My heart sank again.

But the group always received reports from Peng Yinhua, said that today's stable vital signs, said colleagues eat more, nutrition to keep up.

On February 9th, after he confessed to having "a temperature fluctuation, " there was no more news, and everyone panicked. Until the next morning, he suddenly appeared, "almost did not see you. ". The night before, he had a fever of 38.3 C and a 50% Oxygenation for an hour or two, and the team at the pool of gold and silver temporarily added a small dose of hormones to ease his breathing and considered intubation

Chen felt bad, but he never heard Peng Yinhua say any negative, Cathartic words, the lowest just said: I saw the side of the bed grandma just left, I realized that death is so close to me.

Colleagues want to do something, he said to please 120 to bring a change of clothes, but also hope to send some supplies to his wife, she does not have much. It was February 10th, as if everyone had lost touch with him since.

That afternoon, Peng Yinhua was intubated and in a deep coma. "From non-invasive to invasive, we know it's not very promising, and at this point, most patients are very difficult to treat, " Yin said. Chen Hao thought the prognosis may not be too good, "but do not want to think more, hold great hope for him, you around such a person, said he would die in the line of duty, not to that point, you do not want to think, do not want to believe, also did not prepare. "

Get the first batch of rehabilitation of plasma, Chen Hao immediately thought can be used for Peng Yinhua, check the blood type, the three bags a total of 300 ml of plasma sent to the gold and Silver Lake.

Jiang Junxia always thinking about Peng Yinhua, can not help but contact with Zhong Xin, "Peng Yinhua now how? " Zhong Xin also no news, also comfort said, "no news is good news. ".

Finally, Jiang contacted Professor Yu Zhui of the provincial people's hospital through a classmate. He was leading a team to treat Peng Yinhua. Professor Yu said Peng's pancreatic enzyme (an indicator of severe pancreatitis) had come up, which meant that the pancreas had also been damaged. And the ASCITES, the CRRT was on the verge of becoming an organ, and the kidneys, too, were failing.

Peng Yinhua is in hospital

If only 2020 hadn't come along

Just after 21:50 on February 20,2020, Jiang Junxia received a message from Professor Yu Zhui, "I've come down from the ward and done my best, " she told Chen Hao. "Peng Yinhua is no longer here, " she said.

The head nurse asked in the department's Wechat Group, "are they all here? "

Several people replied "Yes" and "I am" . No one said anything, and everyone guessed it. Yin Dequn was in a daze and his hands were shaking, but he had work to do and a large number of patients who dared not let their grief rise.

Back in those days, Dr. Li Dan could find no other word to describe it than "thrilling. ".

A few outspoken, usually love and Peng Yinhua to chat with the nurses, have not slept all night, 3 o'clock at night really can not hold open a group of calls.

Jiang Junxia, who lives in the isolation ward, cried all night without talking to anyone. The aunt in the next bed comforted her, "you are a patient now, to adjust themselves. ". Two days later she wrote in her diary: Cry Today, don't cry tomorrow. She also remembered not long ago and Peng Yinhua in hospital together, about to write a diary, one day she wrote "The Sun came, very warm" , Yin Dequn doctor smiled said she really good state of mind. She wondered if Peng Yinhua had written it.

On the 23rd, the end of the isolation of Dr. Li Yingpu back to the department, rounds to see Peng Yinhua once the bed, next to the bed of Jiang Junxia eye is still swollen. "As a doctor, I didn't protect my colleagues, " Ms. Li sobbed, "although it's true that clinicians go through a lot of death and loss, and a lot of people think we're hard-hearted and cold-blooded and that our duty is there, and we can't put our weakness in front of our patients, to be honest, it's very upsetting to have this happen to a colleague, to have a fellow soldier fall... "

Epidemic situation is still continuing, Li Ying Pu know to continue to shield the heart of a lot of feelings. "It never occurred to me that in peacetime we would 'fight' on the front lines, " he said. "If you say you are afraid, you are indeed afraid. If you are a medical worker, you are indeed not afraid. If you wear a white coat and a protective suit, you will not allow yourself to shrink back. We doctors and nurses after the quarantine period to return to the front line, in fact, our parents do not want us to continue to work, my cousin said my parents haggard, I can not imagine Peng Yinhua's parents now. But it's our job. As long as this outbreak holds, we can't back down. Now, not only because we are medical workers, but because so many of our brothers and sisters from all over the country have come to support us, they are human beings, and for their sake, we must go back to war and give them rest. We are one."

Jiang Junxia is also reconfirming her belief. She believed that a repeat of such a campaign would not be held back, that people would accept patients without hesitation, but that there would be lessons to be learned. "We're all back from Corey's quarantine. I'll be back when I'm cured. "

These days, Chen Hao thinks a lot, he is the hardest kind of person. It was not the first time he had faced a serious situation, but "it was definitely the worst" and he knew he had to lead his team into it. "after Dr. Peng's death, we had depression and psychological trauma, but we were still working actively, otherwise our colleagues would have died in vain. "

For more than a month, he and his team struggled to maintain the function of the patients'damaged organs and help them overcome the virus's self-limitation. "after this outbreak, I think humans are like frogs in a well. Our knowledge is so limited that when you think you know a pattern and think everything is going according to your experience, it may come to a Black Swan. You think you understand the laws of the world, but the real laws are not what you think they are, you must always be in awe, our doctors, scientists can not be too confident, we must be in awe of nature, of science, just like this disease, beyond recognition. Our work, including doctors'infections, is proving that more than your experience is happening."

There was another lament among colleagues: The year 2020 is not here yet, and without the virus, he is still..

Photograph by Zhao Ying, my shot

120 Love

Zhong Xin always remembers when he was working as a 120-year-old nurse in the First Hospital of Jiangxia, every time he and Peng Yinhua gave first aid. Peng had just graduated from university and was working as an 120-year-old first aid doctor. Car Accidents, fires, violence, the two have faced many deaths together.

It was raining in the early hours of January 2016, and they got a phone call and rushed to the Jiangxia District funeral home, where they were involved in a medical dispute. The victim's body was still warm, but the hospital had pronounced him clinically dead, his family made a scene, and they brought in a bunch of people. The scene was chaotic. Peng Yinhua has been protecting Zhong Xin, while trying to communicate with the family. Family members forced the patient on the car, Peng Yinhua or to do CPR, venipuncture and oxygen, and try to complete their own, do not let Zhong Xin.

Zhong Xin recalled, "It wasn't my first time with him, but I was very impressed. We went to the police station to give a statement afterwards. I was very nervous. The first time I came to the police station, he told me not to be afraid and said, 'I haven't been through this either. Just tell me what happened. ' "

Not long after that, they got together. On November 30,2017, the day of the collection, it was Zhong Xin's birthday.

The couple has been living with her parents and brother in a small bungalow since their marriage. Both parents worked odd jobs for a living. Peng Yinhua's father lost his ability to work after a stroke in 2014, his mother suffered from high blood pressure for many years, and Zhong Xin's father also had high blood pressure in 2008 and had two kidney stone operations, the old people of both families have been taking medicine for years. When she became pregnant and left her job, Peng became the sole breadwinner for both families, working hard to save money for a house, a better environment for the unborn darling, and a father who had suffered a stroke. Today, the Tencent Holdings who donated money to him says "killed in the line of duty. " .

"He's actually quite quiet at home, playing games when he's relaxing and being a workaholic at work; I like Reading Psychology Books, and lately I've been reading parenting books, " Zhong said. So far, darling hasn't picked a name.

At 1:47 p.m. on February 10, Zhong Xin received her husband's last message that he had asked the head nurse of the Department to help prepare some medicine and supplies for the family.

All through the night on February 20, Zhong Xin was shaking and trying to control it. She was afraid that the baby was in danger and was trying not to cry. "I've been repressing my emotions and I think of myself as a very strong person. "

On March 2, it was cloudy again in Wuhan, and the streets were wet.

As the fetus grew, Zhong Xin walked a little sideways, but not a small step, through a crowd of pregnant women and accompanying husbands. She climbed five flights of stairs to get a mid-term ovulatory exam. The image of the fetus appeared on the ultrasound machine, the doctor told her, "the fetus is right now hand block the face, the face of the three-dimensional, facial features are normal AH. "

"All blocked! " Zhong Xin's tone was a little higher, with a trace of excitement.

She knew how much courage it took to raise a child, and now she just wanted to keep darling alive so that the child would grow up to be a hero.
